  "prompt": "Can you see someone's status message if they block you on WhatsApp?",
  "response": "No, if someone blocks you on WhatsApp, you will not be able to see their status updates. Here\u2019s what happens when you are blocked on WhatsApp:\n\n1. **Status Updates**: You will no longer see their profile photo, about info, or status updates.\n2. **Messages**: Any messages you send will remain with a single grey tick (not delivered).\n3. **Calls**: You won\u2019t be able to call them, and your calls won\u2019t go through.\n4. **Last Seen**: Their \u201clast seen\u201d timestamp will no longer appear to you.\n5. **Profile Changes**: If they change their profile photo or name, you won\u2019t see the updates.\n\nIn summary, you are essentially cut off from seeing any of their activity on WhatsApp once they block you.",
